The paper discusses a neuroscience method to understand the brain and its application in debugging and explaining networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with neural networks, computer vision, machine learning, artificial intelligence, and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
